title: Romance of War ... New edition
author: Grant, James
snippet: I succeeded my father in the humbleoccupation of gardener to the family of this Monsieur Maurice de Mesmai,at the castle of Quinsay, a noble chateau, built on the banks of theDoubs, which flows through Besangon.

title: Romance of War ... New edition
author: Grant, James
snippet: ' What! the gardener at my jovial old Chateau of Quinsay, on the banksof the Doubs ? Impossible ! he was destroyed when I blew up the hall,with all the base republican mechanics who filled it.'
